      <section id="purpose" class="cd-purpose">
        <h2>Purpose/Theme</h2>

        <div class="cd-box"><p>Our Zen Garden webpage will have a futuristic look. We like technology, and we like innovation. Some of the web pages design that we found online gave us great insights; some of them were too cluttered, some of them looked too simple and we decided to mix both together. The futuristic theme has images, it divides each session/talking point of the web page nicely. The futuristic version of the Zen Garden also includes animations such as flipping when the object is hovered over and buttons will also change their appearance. To give this theme an extra futuristic look, we will have a small division, “The Beauty of CSS Design” to be auto-completed, character by character will appear on the web page once it’s fully loaded. This part will be achieved as we use animations and transformation. To achieve a responsive web page, we will use Sass mixins and selectors. And, to make our code simpler, reusable, and scalable, we will use variables for colors, we will use classes as selectors, and only if applicable, we will nest functionality within its corresponding class.</p></div>
